item.title: Thermomix TM6 (and TM5) Egg Splitter and Funnel
item.description:
2 objects to be printed here - a funnel and an egg splitter that both fit in the hole of the Thermomix cover.

I designed them for the TM6 but the hole size is the same so they should also work for TM5.

Use FOOD SAFE filament- PETG for example.

I printed with 3 walls which makes it sturdy.

Tip to use the egg splitter:

  • Put in the cap hole
  • Crack the egg in it
  • Slowly spin the egg splitted in the hole (not to hard)

I included the Fusion 360 file if anybody wants to modify it.

item.title: Pipe Clamp Adapter
item.description:
This is an adapter for firmly grasping the pipe without crushing it. Compatible with pipes from 2 mm to 12 mm.

[Design points]
-A pair of adapters are combined so it's easy to find from the toolbox
-Since the adapter can be opened with one hand like a clip, it is easy to pinch the pipe and set it in a vise.
-Since the size are 1 mm steps, it can handle an intermediate pipe size (for example, 9.5 mm).

-[print conditions]
-filament: PETG
-support: no
-brim: no
-raft: doesn't matter

item.title: Customizable Stand for Articulated Dragon
item.description:
My design inspired from https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5178556

This is fully customizable, you can print off your own designs to attach to base and top of pole, or not.

Use glue to attach pole to stand.

I have included separate files to be able to print the base and pole in different colors, just glue together. I also included an alternate for top of pole.

Not a big fan of supports, All files printed support free.

I printed the rings in the same color as the stand Rings do have different dimensions you will need 2 of the Top/Middle ring.

Find the Dragon STL here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/articulated-dragon-mcgybeer

Je recommande le PETG il sera plus résistant que le PLA, Il faudra changer les vis de fixation plus longue.

item.title: Lipo charger button repair without soldering
item.description:
I need to remove the pcb from the case but its impossible to do without removing the original buttons, the original buttons are tight fit to the switches, when you try to pull you break the switches :(, mines are impossible to remove, tried with heat and other tricks and nothing works.

I know that this charger is the typical chinese copy that has a lot of versions with different case but same pcb, I put two versions of the buttons that you can select the one that fits with your charguer.

Mine uses two piece version.

if you have a switch with partial dmg you need to remove debris from the switch, if not the switch works glitchy… I recomend to upgrade your damage from light to full damage, clean the switch and use the bigger buttons.

You can see that the screw can fit below the case, this is important.

Recomend to print this in ASA or ABS due high temperatures that charger reaches, the top buttons of 2 piece version you can print in TPU.

item.title: PCB stand-off
item.description:
This is a simple stand-off that can be used when adding additional modules or boards to something already created.

The current height is 7mm

The first one I uploaded is 7.5mm OD and 2.5mm ID to facilitate a 3mm threaded ID. It was also meant to be glued down.

The second is 8mm OD and 3mm ID for a through screw mount.
